    "created_at": "2019-02-15T15:34:45Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-02-15T15:35:17Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "This fails on Windows. Not sure but seems like Sphinx removes the \"\\\\\" from `os.path.join` and can't find files on `savefig_dir` when rendering html.\r\n\r\nI have also set `ipython_savefig_dir` in `conf.py` and the images are saved in the right directory.\r\n\r\nUsing it right now for documenting a Windows app, so to make it work, I simply added\r\n```python\r\nif os.name == 'nt':\r\n     outfile = outfile.replace('\\\\', '/')\r\n```\r\nNot sure if it's the best way."
